You're missing the **`BindingContext`**. The `{Binding}` markup works, but MAUI doesn't know *what* object to bind against.

**Fix — set the `BindingContext`** in your code-behind:

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

Also make sure your ViewModel implements **`INotifyPropertyChanged`** (or inherits `ObservableObject` from the MVVM Toolkit) so the UI updates when properties change:

```csharp
public class MyViewModel : INotifyPropertyChanged
{
    private string _title = "Hello";
    public string Title
    {
        get => _title;
        set { _title = value; OnPropertyChanged(); }
    }
    // ... same for Description

    public event PropertyChangedEventHandler? PropertyChanged;
    void OnPropertyChanged([CallerMemberName] string n = "")
        => PropertyChanged?.Invoke(this, new PropertyChangedEventArgs(n));
}
```

**TL;DR:** No `BindingContext` → bindings resolve against `null` → blank labels.
